facts.seriesTitle: Population below international poverty line (percent)
facts.fact_text: The proportion of the population living below the extreme poverty line declined from 3 % in 1992 to 0.1% in 2016.

facts.seriesTitle: Employed population below international poverty line (percent)
facts.fact_text: In 2016, 0.0 % of the country's workers and their families were living on less than 1.90 US dollars per person per day

facts.seriesTitle: Proportion of population living below the national poverty line (percent)
facts.fact_text: The proportion of population living below the national poverty line declined from 83.3 % in 2002 to 2.4% in 2017.

facts.seriesTitle: Score of adoption and implementation of national DRR strategies in line with the Sendai Framework
facts.fact_text: The score of adoption and implementation of national disaster and risk reduction strategies was approximately 0.5 % in 2018.

facts.seriesTitle: Prevalence of undernourishment (percent)

facts.fact_text: In 2000, 22.9 % of children under 5 years of age had stunted growth

facts.seriesTitle: Proportion of children under 5 years of age who are moderately or severely overweight
facts.fact_text: The share of overweight children under 5 years of age was approximately26.5 % in 2000.

facts.seriesTitle: Maternal mortality ratio
facts.fact_text: The maternal mortality ratio decreased from 46 per 100,000 live births in 1990 to 24 per 100,000 live births in 2015.

facts.seriesTitle: Under-five mortality rate
facts.fact_text: The mortality rate of children under 5 years of age fell from 18.5 per 1,000 live births in 2000 to 8.8 per 1,000 live births in 2017.

facts.seriesTitle: Number of new HIV infections per 1,000 uninfected population
facts.fact_text: In 2017, there were about 0.29 people in every 100,000 uninfected population that became newly infected with HIV.

facts.seriesTitle: Gender parity index for achievement in mathematics by the end of primary education
facts.fact_text: The gender parity index for achievement in mathematics at the end of primary education was 1.02 in 2007 , meaning 102.0 girls per 100 boys achieved at least a minimum proficiency level in mathematics.

facts.seriesTitle: Proportion of women aged 20-24 years who were married or in a union before age 18 (percent)
facts.fact_text: In 2012, 9.1 % of women between 20 to 24 years of age reported having been married before their eighteenth birthday

facts.seriesTitle: Proportion of seats held by women in national parliaments (percent)
facts.fact_text: The proportion of seats held by women in single or lower houses of parliament increased from 7.78 % in 2000 to 11.58% in 2019.

facts.seriesTitle: Proportion of population with access to electricity (percent)

facts.seriesTitle: Proportion of population with primary reliance on clean fuels and technology (percent)

facts.seriesTitle: Annual growth rate of real GDP per capita (percent)

facts.seriesTitle: Domestic material consumption per capita (tonnes)

facts.seriesTitle: Unemployment rate of population 15 years of age and older

facts.seriesTitle: Proportion of population covered by at least a 2G mobile network (percent)

facts.seriesTitle: Proportion of urban population living in slums (percent)

facts.seriesTitle: Annual mean levels of fine particulate matter in cities (micrograms per cubic meter)
facts.fact_text: In 2016, the annual population-weighted average mean concentration of fine suspended particles of less than 2.5 microns in diameter (PM2.5) was about 18.29 micrograms per cubic metre. This is above the maximum level for safety set by WHO of 10 micrograms per cubic metre.

facts.seriesTitle: Volume of remittances as a proportion of total GCP (percent)

facts.seriesTitle: Debt service as a proportion of exports of goods and services (percent)

facts.seriesTitle: Fixed internet broadband subscriptions per 100 inhabitants
